result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Case called: 1:49pm. Clerk: Denise. INCLUDES 14CF779, 15CM144. State appears by ADA Kyle Mayo. Defendant appears by Atty Dave Casey. State files Amended Information in 14CF779 along with filing of new complaint 15CM144. Crt proceeds with Initial on 15CM144. W/R. Plea: Not Guilty. Crt addresses Amended Information filed in 14CF779. Defense in agreement and W/R. Crt proceeds with Plea. 
Plea Quest/Waiver of Rights & Counsel filed. State moves to DRI ct 1 (poss w/intent-pilocin);  ct 3 (manufact/deliver-psilocin); ct 4 (manufact/deliever thc) 14CF779 - crt grants. State moves to DRI 15CM144- crt grants.  
PLEA: NO CONTEST - ct 2 (poss w/int deliever thc); amend ct 5 (drug para); amend ct 6 (poss thc)14CF779. Crt advises def of rights & penalties & ques def to understanding.  Crt finds plea & waiver freely & vol made, a factual basis & def deferred on amend ct 2 and guilty on cts 5 & 6. 
Statements by State & Defense.
COURT ORDERS: Amended cts 5 & 6- SWH 1 yr probation, concurent. CONDITIONS: Counseling; Absolute Sobriety; AODA; Good faith effort to obtain and maintain fulltime employment and/or school;  Court Costs; DNA Surcharge.  OURT FURTHER ORDERS:  ct 2 (poss w/int to deliver thc) - DEOJ - 2 yrs probation. Crt adopts & signs Deferred Entry of Judgment. DATES: Review Hearing 1/11/17 @ 1:10pm. Adjourned: 2:06pm.
